# BTRS Agents -- Windsurf Instructions

See **AGENTS.md** for the full BTRS instruction set. This file adds Windsurf/Codeium-specific patterns.

## Setup

### Option 1: Global (all projects)

```bash
# Clone BTRS
git clone https://github.com/btrs-ai/btrs.git ~/.btrs

# Symlink rules so they auto-load
ln -sf ~/.btrs/.windsurfrules ~/.windsurfrules
```

Then in Cascade, reference agents with `@~/.btrs/agents/btrs-architect/AGENT.md`.

### Option 2: Per-project

```bash
git clone https://github.com/btrs-ai/btrs.git .btrs-agents
```

The `.windsurfrules` file auto-loads. Reference agents with `@.btrs-agents/agents/btrs-architect/AGENT.md`.

## How to Use BTRS in Windsurf

### Loading Agent Context with Cascade
Use @file to bring agent instructions into Cascade context:
- `@agents/btrs-architect/AGENT.md` -- for architecture work
- `@agents/btrs-api-engineer/AGENT.md` -- for backend APIs
- `@agents/btrs-web-engineer/AGENT.md` -- for frontend work
- `@agents/btrs-database-engineer/AGENT.md` -- for database work
- `@agents/btrs-code-security/AGENT.md` -- for security review
- `@AGENTS.md` -- universal instructions (load this for every session)

See AGENTS.md for the full list of 24 agents.

### Cascade Workflow
1. Start by loading `@AGENTS.md` for conventions
2. Load the relevant agent's AGENT.md for the domain you're working in
3. Ask Cascade to plan the work before implementing
4. Review the plan and approve
5. Cascade implements following agent scope and conventions
6. Verify using the 5-point protocol from AGENTS.md

### Multi-File Edits
When Cascade proposes multi-file changes:
- Ensure changes stay within the assigned agent's scope
- Check that imports resolve and types are consistent
- Verify new code follows `.btrs/conventions/` rules

## Conventions (from AGENTS.md)
1. Check `.btrs/conventions/registry.md` before creating new components or utilities
2. Follow the 5-point verification protocol after changes
3. Match existing codebase patterns exactly
4. Update `.btrs/` vault files after completing work (code-map, todos, changelog)
